The paper deals with distributed computing, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper specifically focuses on the LOCAL model, which is a model for studying locality in distributed network computing, and this falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the impact of asynchrony and failures on the LOCAL model, which relates to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
